# Git mailmap — remaps committer/author identities at display time without
# touching commit objects. Honoured by `git log`, `git blame`, `git shortlog`,
# `git check-mailmap`, and GitHub's contributor pages.
#
# Format used here:
#   <canonical-name> <canonical-email>  <commit-name> <commit-email>
#
# Scope: the polluted `test@example.com` identity that leaked from vitest
# fixtures into the developer's local git config (root cause and guard:
# T9149, vitest.setup.ts + .github/workflows/identity-pollution-check.yml).
# All three observed surface variants — `Test`, lowercase `test`, and the
# `Drift Test` drift-watchdog leak — map back to the project owner's
# canonical GitHub identity.
#
# Legitimate fixture identities (`cleo-test`, `CLEO Test`, `cleo-agent`,
# `cleo-subagent`, etc.) are intentionally left untouched — those are
# scoped agent identities, not impersonations of the owner.

kryptobaseddev <kryptobaseddev@users.noreply.github.com>  Test <test@example.com>
kryptobaseddev <kryptobaseddev@users.noreply.github.com>  test <test@example.com>
kryptobaseddev <kryptobaseddev@users.noreply.github.com>  Drift Test <test@example.com>
